[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326921&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326921&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I have a question:

   I run bind 4.8 and am administrator for dsi.com, I been wondering
what is an authoritive answer?

   I have the SOA records in my database for dsi.com, yet when I query
the name server for myself, I get back a non-authoritive answer.
Thinking, perhaps I have a bad database setup, I tried changing
the server I was quering to several others including phlsun.prepnet.com
and uunet.uu.net, and in each case queried itself about itself.  In each
case I got back a non-authoritive answer.

So, what is an authoritive answer and when should bind return one?
When should a bind request demand one, an how?

Please respond by e-mail, and I will summarize to the net.
-- 
